    "This sampling process can be intuitively described as refining internal angles from an unfolded state towards a folded state.",
    "For our reverse (denoising) p ξ x t,t À Á, we adopt a vanilla bidirectional transformer architecture 58 with relative positional embeddings 59.",
    "Our six-dimensional input is linearly upscaled to the model's embedding dimension (d = 384).",
    "To incorporate the timestep t, we generate random Fourier feature embeddings 60 as done in ref.",
    "61 and add these embeddings to each upscaled input."
